---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Wall Timeline" activeTab="timeline">
  <div class="mb-8">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="tier-badge bg-timeline/20 text-timeline text-sm">Wall Timeline</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold">24 Months to University</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mt-2">
      <strong>Melbourne</strong> (reach) &middot; <strong>Waseda</strong> (target) &middot; <strong>Shibaura</strong> (safety)
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card border-timeline/40 mb-12">
    <p class="text-lg text-white font-semibold m-0">
      Grade 11 grades, AP scores, and SAT are the only thing universities will see when they make a decision.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-2 mb-0">
      Grade 12 first-semester grades arrive too late to change a decision. The next twelve months are the ones that count.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Target numbers to hit</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="content-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Metric</th>
            <th>Floor (Melbourne / Shibaura)</th>
            <th>Target (Waseda)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Unweighted GPA</td>
            <td>3.5</td>
            <td class="text-waseda font-bold">3.7+</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>SAT (digital)</td>
            <td>1320</td>
            <td class="text-waseda font-bold">1450+</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>TOEFL iBT</td>
            <td>80</td>
            <td class="text-waseda font-bold">95+</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>AP exams with score &ge; 4</td>
            <td><strong>3 minimum</strong> including Calc + Physics</td>
            <td class="text-waseda font-bold">4+</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Grade 11 — 2026/27 <span class="text-timeline text-base font-normal">(the decisive year)</span></h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="mt-0 text-base flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-timeline">Summer 2026</span>
          <span class="text-gray-600">Jun-Aug — Foundation</span>
        </h3>
        <ul class="checklist text-sm mb-0">
          <li>Choose Grade 11 courses: <strong>AP Calculus AB, AP Physics 1 (or C: Mechanics), AP Chemistry</strong></li>
          <li>Start SAT prep — <strong>30 min/day, every day</strong> (Khan Academy SAT is free and official)</li>
          <li>Pick one engineering project to work on over the summer (build, repair, restore something)</li>
          <li>Bring academic Japanese back up — 30 min/day reading</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="mt-0 text-base flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-timeline">Fall 2026</span>
          <span class="text-gray-600">Sep-Dec — Routines</span>
        </h3>
        <ul class="checklist text-sm mb-0">
          <li><strong>Take PSAT on October 14, 2026</strong> (free diagnostic)</li>
          <li>Join <strong>one</strong> sustained extracurricular and <strong>stay in it</strong> through Grade 12</li>
          <li>Q1 + Q2 grades — target <strong>all A's and B's</strong></li>
          <li>Begin 1-hour-a-week engineering reading habit</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="mt-0 text-base flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-timeline">Winter 2026/27</span>
          <span class="text-gray-600">Jan-Mar — Push on tests</span>
        </h3>
        <ul class="checklist text-sm mb-0">
          <li>Increase SAT prep to <strong>1 hour/day</strong></li>
          <li>Take <strong>one full timed SAT practice test per month</strong> (Bluebook app)</li>
          <li>Q3 grades — target <strong>all A's and B's</strong></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="mt-0 text-base flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-timeline">Spring 2027</span>
          <span class="text-gray-600">Apr-Jun — Test phase</span>
        </h3>
        <ul class="checklist text-sm mb-0">
          <li><strong>First SAT: May 2027</strong> — target 1320+ (1450+ for Waseda)</li>
          <li><strong>AP exams: May 5-16, 2027</strong> — Calculus, Physics, Chemistry</li>
          <li><strong>TOEFL iBT: July 2027</strong> — target 90+ (95+ for Waseda)</li>
          <li>End of year: have <strong>transcript, SAT score, and AP scores in hand</strong></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="mt-0 text-base flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-timeline">Summer 2027</span>
          <span class="text-gray-600">Jun-Aug — Build the application</span>
        </h3>
        <ul class="checklist text-sm mb-0">
          <li>Attend <strong>one STEM summer program</strong> (online or in Japan)</li>
          <li>Begin drafting <strong>Statement of Purpose</strong> for Waseda (~800 words)</li>
          <li>Begin <strong>Personal Statement</strong> for Melbourne (~500-1,000 words)</li>
          <li>Create <strong>TAO platform account</strong> for Shibaura IGP</li>
          <li>If SAT &lt; 1450: register for <strong>October 2027 retake</strong></li>
          <li>Start preparing <strong>3-5 minute video</strong> for Shibaura IGP</li>
          <li>Identify two teachers for recommendation letters</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Grade 12 — 2027/28 <span class="text-timeline text-base font-normal">(the application year)</span></h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="mt-0 text-base flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-timeline">Fall 2027</span>
          <span class="text-gray-600">Aug-Nov — Submit</span>
        </h3>
        <ul class="checklist text-sm mb-0">
          <li><strong>August 1, 2027:</strong> Melbourne application opens — start filling it out immediately</li>
          <li><strong>October 2, 2027:</strong> SAT retake if needed</li>
          <li><strong>Request recommendation letters by Nov 15</strong> (give teachers 6+ weeks)</li>
          <li class="font-semibold text-shibaura">November 4-18, 2027: Shibaura IGP application window — SUBMIT BY NOV 10</li>
          <li><strong>November 15, 2027:</strong> Submit Melbourne application</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="mt-0 text-base flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-timeline">Winter 2027/28</span>
          <span class="text-gray-600">Dec-Mar — Apply + wait</span>
        </h3>
        <ul class="checklist text-sm mb-0">
          <li><strong>December 2027:</strong> Melbourne first offers begin arriving</li>
          <li class="font-semibold text-waseda">January 8 - February 10, 2028: Waseda application window — SUBMIT BY JAN 25</li>
          <li><strong>January 23, 2028:</strong> Shibaura first screening results</li>
          <li><strong>February 15, 2028:</strong> Shibaura online interview + maths/physics test</li>
          <li><strong>March 26, 2028:</strong> Shibaura final decision</li>
          <li><strong>March 31, 2028:</strong> Waseda decision</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="mt-0 text-base flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-timeline">Spring 2028</span>
          <span class="text-gray-600">Apr-Jun — Decide + enrol</span>
        </h3>
        <ul class="checklist text-sm mb-0">
          <li><strong>April 2028:</strong> Compare offers, accept one, pay deposit</li>
          <li><strong>AP exams: May 2028</strong> — these matter for Melbourne offer conditions</li>
          <li><strong>May 26, 2028:</strong> OCSI graduation</li>
          <li><strong>April-July 2028:</strong> Status of Residence transfer (Japan) OR student visa (Australia)</li>
          <li><strong>July 2028:</strong> Confirm accommodation</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="mt-0 text-base flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-timeline">Summer 2028</span>
          <span class="text-gray-600">Jun-Sep — Transition</span>
        </h3>
        <ul class="checklist text-sm mb-0">
          <li class="text-waseda font-semibold">September 21, 2028: Waseda semester begins (or Shibaura ~Sept 25)</li>
          <li class="text-melbourne font-semibold">February 26, 2029: Melbourne Semester 1 begins</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>The full picture</h2>
    <div class="mermaid-container">
      <pre class="mermaid">
gantt
    title  Ivan — 24 Months to University
    dateFormat  YYYY-MM-DD
    axisFormat  %b %Y

    section Tests
    SAT prep                          :2026-09-01, 240d
    PSAT                              :milestone, 2026-10-14, 0d
    First SAT                         :milestone, 2027-05-01, 0d
    AP exams 2027                     :milestone, 2027-05-10, 0d
    TOEFL                             :milestone, 2027-07-15, 0d
    SAT retake                        :milestone, 2027-10-02, 0d
    AP exams 2028                     :milestone, 2028-05-08, 0d

    section Applications
    Melbourne app                     :2027-08-01, 180d
    Shibaura IGP app                  :2027-11-04, 14d
    Waseda app                        :2028-01-08, 33d

    section Decisions
    Melbourne (rolling)               :2027-12-15, 75d
    Shibaura decision                 :milestone, 2028-03-26, 0d
    Waseda decision                   :milestone, 2028-03-31, 0d

    section Enrolment
    Visa + accommodation              :2028-04-01, 150d
    Graduate OCSI                     :milestone, 2028-05-26, 0d
    Start Waseda/Shibaura             :milestone, 2028-09-21, 0d
    Start Melbourne                   :milestone, 2029-02-26, 0d
      </pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Daily habits <span class="text-timeline text-base font-normal">(the part that determines the outcome)</span></h2>
    <div class="card border-timeline/30">
      <p class="mb-4">The dates above are not what fail. What fails is the <strong>30 minutes a day</strong> that doesn't happen.</p>
      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="bg-surface-700 rounded-lg p-4">
          <p class="text-timeline font-bold text-sm mb-1">Habit 1</p>
          <p class="text-sm mb-0"><strong>30 minutes of SAT/TOEFL prep</strong> — even on weekends. Skip a day, you lose two days catching up.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-surface-700 rounded-lg p-4">
          <p class="text-timeline font-bold text-sm mb-1">Habit 2</p>
          <p class="text-sm mb-0"><strong>30 minutes of academic reading</strong> in the target subject — pick the topic, but show up.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-4 mb-0">
        These two habits, sustained for 18 months, are worth more than any single test prep course or summer program.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>What dad will help with, what is yours</h2>
    <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="mt-0 text-base text-gray-400">Dad's job</h3>
        <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 list-none pl-0 mb-0">
          <li>Pay for tests, programs, applications</li>
          <li>Drive to test centres</li>
          <li>Talk through option trade-offs</li>
          <li>Review essay drafts</li>
          <li>Help with visa paperwork</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card border-timeline/30">
        <h3 class="mt-0 text-base text-timeline">Your job</h3>
        <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 list-none pl-0 mb-0">
          <li>Show up to study every day</li>
          <li>Take the tests</li>
          <li>Pick which one feels right</li>
          <li>Write the essays</li>
          <li>Build the record they will read</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mt-6 border-timeline/40 text-center">
      <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-0">
        No one can do the daily work for you. This document exists because you said you wanted mechanical engineering. The path is open. Walking it is on you.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
